fields.etr_issue_desc: Unknown hydrophone issue - data are okay pre-deployment, but all data after deployment are compromised; hydrophone dead upon recovery. No sign of corrosion on the hydrophone cable or hydrophone/AMAR connectors.
Hydrophone had a delamination issue, and showed a sensitivity change of 1.54 dB in air after recovery. Negligible/non-detectable effect on recordings.
Hydrophone had a delamination issue, and showed a sensitivity change of 6.4 dB in air after recovery. Negligible/non-detectable effect on recordings.

AMAR 143 had no memory securing tywraps when opened during demobilization. The memory stack was slightly skewed, but there is data on the stack with the expected duration. No data loss, but JASCO will create an internal issue about this for tracking and resolution.
